'''Fredrik Aursnes''' (born 10 December 1995) is a Norwegian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays primarily as a [[midfielder]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]]. He is renowned for his high work rate and has also been successfully deployed as a [[Forward (association football)#Winger|winger]] and a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|full-back]] on both flanks.

==Club career==
===Early career===
Aursnes played youth football for [[Hareid IL|Hareid]], before joining [[IL Hødd|Hødd]] before the 2012 season. He made his senior league debut in April 2012 in a 2–1 win against [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]]. Aged 16 years and 350 days, he became the all-time youngest winner and youngest finalist of the [[Norwegian Football Cup|Norwegian Cup]] after Hødd's win against [[Tromsø IL]] in the [[2012 Norwegian Football Cup Final|final]].

===Molde===
In December 2015, Aursnes joined [[Molde FK|Molde]] on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nrk.no/mr/aursnes-til-molde-1.12681118 |title=Aursnes til Molde |trans-title=Aursnes to Molde |website=www.nrk.no |publisher=NRK |date=1 December 2015 |access-date=11 March 2019}}</ref> He debuted on 18 February 2016 against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] in the [[UEFA Europa League]] round of 32, first leg. On 22 April 2019, Aursnes got his 100th first-team appearance for the club in their 2–0 away win against [[Lillestrøm SK|Lillestrøm]]. On 30 April 2019, Aursnes signed a two-year contract extension that ties him to Molde until the end of the 2021 season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hestad og Aursnes forlenger|url=https://www.moldefk.no/nyheter/hestad-og-aursnes-forlenger|website=www.moldefk.no|publisher=Molde FK |access-date=30 April 2019|language=no|date=30 April 2019}}</ref> On 11 July 2019, he scored Molde's second goal in the club's [[UEFA competitions]] record 7–1 win over [[Knattspyrnufélag Reykjavíkur|KR]] in the [[UEFA Europa League]] first qualifying round.<ref>{{cite web|title=Molde 7-1 KR |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/07/11/europe/uefa-cup/molde-fotballklubb/knattspyrnufelagid-reykjavik/3033993/|website=www.soccerway.com|publisher=Soccerway|access-date=11 July 2019|date=12 July 2019}}</ref>

===Feyenoord===
On 8 August 2021, following their 5–4 victory over [[FK Haugesund|Haugesund]], Molde announced that Aursnes had been sold to [[Feyenoord]].<ref>{{cite web |title=FREDRIK AURSNES ER KLAR FOR FEYENOORD! |url=https://www.moldefk.no/nyheter/fredrik-aursnes-er-klar-for-feyenoord |website=moldefk.no/ |publisher=Molde FK |access-date=8 August 2021 |language=Norwegian |date=8 August 2021}}</ref> On 10 August 2021, Aursnes signed a three-year contract at the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=Feyenoord contracteert middenvelder Fredrik Aursnes |url=https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/feyenoord-contracteert-middenvelder-aursnes---100821 |website=moldefk.no/ |publisher=Feyenoord |language=Dutch |date=10 August 2021 |access-date=10 August 2021}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Feyenoord against [[SC Cambuur]], in a 3–2 victory on 24 October 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Feyenoord laat Cambuur spartelen en zegeviert met minimaal verschil: 3-2|url=https://nos.nl/l/2402960|access-date=25 October 2021|website=nos.nl|date=24 October 2021 |language=nl}}</ref>

===Benfica===
On 24 August 2022, Aursnes signed a five-year contract with [[Primeira Liga]] side [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], for a reported fee of €13 million plus €2 million in add-ons.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abola.pt/amp/2022-08-24/benfica-oficial-aursnes-e-reforco-das-aguias-os-pormenores-do-negocio/954163|title=OFICIAL: AURSNES É REFORÇO DAS ÁGUIAS (OS PORMENORES DO NEGÓCIO)|date=24 August 2022|language=pt|publisher=[[A Bola]]|access-date=25 August 2022|archive-date=12 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221112104301/https://www.abola.pt/amp/2022-08-24/benfica-oficial-aursnes-e-reforco-das-aguias-os-pormenores-do-negocio/954163|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 27 August, replacing [[Enzo Fernández (footballer, born 2001)|Enzo Fernández]] in the 90th minute in a 3–0 away win over [[FC Boavista|Boavista]] in the [[Primeira Liga]].<ref>{{cite web|date=27 August 2022|title=Schmidt promoveu três estreias no Bessa|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2022-08-27/benfica-schmidt-promoveu-tres-estreias-no-bessa/954561|publisher=[[A Bola]]|access-date=27 August 2022|archive-date=21 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221021001906/https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2022-08-27/benfica-schmidt-promoveu-tres-estreias-no-bessa/954561|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==International career==
Aursnes made his debut for [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]] on 6 June 2021 in a friendly against [[Greece national football team|Greece]]. He substituted [[Patrick Berg]] in the 69th minute.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=600641|title=Norway v Greece game report|date=6 June 2021}}</ref>

On 12 March 2024 national team manager [[Ståle Solbakken]] announced that Aursnes had decided to retire internationally.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Norwegian Football Federation|Norges fotballforbund]]|url=https://www.fotball.no/landslag/norge-a-herrer/2024/aursnes-gir-seg-pa-landslaget/|title=Aursnes gir seg på landslaget|date=12 March 2024}}</ref> However, on 3 February 2026, Aursnes announced that he would be available for selection ahead of the upcoming [[2026 FIFA World Cup|World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Stenersen |first=Steffen |last2=Hopen |first2=Andreas |last3=Overvik |first3=Jostein |last4=Østmoe |first4=Eline Rustad |date=2026-02-03 |title=Fredrik Aursnes gjør comeback for Norge |url=https://www.vg.no/sport/i/k03r9Q/tv-2-aursnes-gjoer-comeback-for-norge |access-date=2026-02-04 |website=VG |language=no}}</ref>

